KAIZER Chiefs head coach Steve Komphela says they are more than ready for their Absa Premiership match against Mamelodi Sundowns at FNB Stadium on Saturday night (8:15pm).Despite raising concern that he always has to play Sundowns after a long break, he has also insisted that he is not shaken by the African Champions.&nbsp;Both teams are still on the run to win the league title and Komphela and Sundowns coach Pitso Mosimane understands that a win will be vital at all cost.However, Mosimane has described his side as underdogs even though the head to head statistics favours them.Chiefs are still yet to beat Sundowns since Komphela joined the Soweto giants.&nbsp;WATCH!